headline: WSM Q3 Deep Dive: AI and Tariff Mitigation Shape Results Amid Mixed Market Reaction
summary: Kitchenware and home goods retailer Williams-Sonoma (NYSE:WSM) reported Q3 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 4.6% year on year to $1.88 billion. Its GAAP profit of $1.96 per share was 4.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
